    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>This could help you. It is a way to handle the touch outside event:</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/4650246/how-to-cancel-an-dialog-themed-like-activity-when-touched-outside-the-window/5831214#5831214\">How to cancel an Dialog themed like Activity when touched outside the window?</a></p>\n\n<p>By catching the event and doing nothing, I think you can prevent the closing. But what is strange though, is that the default behavior of your activity dialog should be <strong>not</strong> to close itself when you touch outside.</p>\n\n<p>(PS: the code uses WindowManager.LayoutParams)</p>\n"
  }, {
