    "creation_date" : 1391701666,
    "answer_id" : 21607500,
    "question_id" : 12102777,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>I was facing the same problem. To handle it I set a <code>OntouchListener</code> to the dialog and do nothing inside. But Dialog dismiss when rotating screen too. To fix it I set a variable to tell me if the dialog has normally dismissed. Then I set a <code>OnDismissListener</code> to my dialog and inside I check the variable. If the dialog has dismmiss normally I do nothin, or else I run the dialog again (and setting his state as when dismissing in my case).</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 4251091,
      "reputation" : 2599,
      "user_id" : 3478155,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 59,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/7bcb030fc6388f9991ba6673cb7a8a5a?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "ilw",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/3478155/ilw"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 20,
    "last_activity_date" : 1398036934,
    "last_edit_date" : 1398036934,
    "creation_date" : 1398031201,
    "answer_id" : 23188044,
    "question_id" : 12102777,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>For higher API 10, the Dialog disappears when on touched outside, whereas in lower than API 11, the Dialog doesn't disappear. For prevent this, you need to do:</p>\n\n<p>In <code>styles.xml</code>: <code>&lt;item name=\"android:windowCloseOnTouchOutside\"&gt;false&lt;/item&gt;</code></p>\n\n<p>OR</p>\n\n<p>In <code>onCreate()</code> method, use: <code>this.setFinishOnTouchOutside(false);</code></p>\n\n<p><em>Note: for API 10 and lower, this method doesn't have effect, and is not needed.</em></p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 2288943,
      "reputation" : 696,
      "user_id" : 2012345,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/kqa2H.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Vishal Pandey",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2012345/vishal-pandey"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 5,
    "last_activity_date" : 1408938341,
    "creation_date" : 1408938341,
    "answer_id" : 25478754,
    "question_id" : 12102777,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Use <code>setFinishOnTouchOutside(false)</code> for API > 11 and don't worry because its android's default behavior that activity themed dialog won't get finished on outside touch for API &lt; 11 :) !!Cheerss!! </p>\n"
  }, {
